ch.ecma.csta.binding

Class SilenceTimeoutExpiredEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • ch.ecma.csta.binding.SilenceTimeoutExpiredEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class SilenceTimeoutExpiredEvent
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Not supported.

    Indicates the silence timeout has expired for an Interactive Voice input device. This event indicates the resource has entered the Null resource state.

    For an illustration of this service, see ECMA 269, section 26.2.11.

    The Completed Event could be caused by the following:

    • The silence timeout has expired.
